Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Macao. The Macao authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus.
The Macao government has announced that all travellers arriving in Macao, who are not residents of Macao, Hong Kong, Taiwan or mainland China, will be denied entry. The Macao government website provides further information.
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
You can find more information about cases in Macao on the TravelHealthPro page.
